  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Customer Service Officer (Tuas)",
  "description": "<h2>Job Description</h2><ul><li>Respond promptly to customer inquiries through various channels (phone call, emails, faxes, etc)</li><li>Liaise, acknowledge and solve customer requests or complaints within stipulated timeline</li><li>Liase with local and overseas suppliers to check stock availabilty, pricing and delivery deadlines</li><li>Liaise with procurement department for enquiry, order, shipments, etc</li><li>Liaise with shipping department for import and export shipments</li><li>Liase with warehouse department to prepare shipments</li><li>Perform daily tasks include preparing quotations, processing orders, backorder tracking, quotation tracking, preparing invoices and other necessary paper work</li><li>Follow-up on quotations, payments</li><li>Prepare contract review, tender files and tender documents</li><li>Understand company's product range in general</li><li>Ad-hoc responsibilities by management</li></ul><h2>Job Requirements</h2><ul><li>At least GCE 'O' Levels or equivalent</li><li>At least 1-2 years working experience in Customer Service or Sales</li><li>Experience in handling overseas suppliers/customers</li><li>Customer service oriented and have a great sense of urgency</li><li>Able to work under pressure in a fast-paced working environment</li><li>Able to work independently and in a team</li><li>Good communication skills</li><li>Meticulous in work and able to do general calculations</li><li>Proficient in MS Excel (VLOOKUP, Pivot Table), and MS Powerpoint</li></ul>",
